The paper deals with the use of lattice codes for secure transmission in wiretap channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The analysis of the eavesdropper's probability of correct decision involves mathematical properties of lattices, which is also relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of skewed lattices for increased security introduces a dimensionality reduction aspect, which is related to signal processing and machine learning (cs.SI, cs.MM).
